///
///   Tips & tricks                                       //f
@node ASENSE-GENERAL-TIPS "ASense - General: Tips & Tricks"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV MAIN
@NEXT MAIN
@{b}@{u}Tips & tricks@{uu}@{ub} - Things that one should know about.

  Q: @{b}When I save chart as a gif ('@{i}Project/Save Chart..@{ui}'), the resulting
     picture looks distorted into an elliptical shape when displayed@{ub}!

  A: @{b}Try using '@{i}GCView@{ui}' (Aminet) as your picture viewer program@{ub}.
     Not only that it displays the gifs correctly, but can do many
     nice things with them too.For example editing and saving them
     as @{i}iff@{ui} files, so that other (dummy) pic viewers can display
     them correctly as well...

     (@{i}Hint@{ui}: Press '@{b}.@{ub}' (full stop) to @{i}toggle interlace@{ui} in GCView.)

@endnode
///
@remark (readme)
///   About                                               //f
@node ASENSE-GENERAL-ABOUT "ASense - General: About"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV MAIN
@NEXT ASENSE-GENERAL-LEGAL
  @{b}@{u}Purpose@{uu}@{ub}:
    The @{b}ASense@{ub} is a @{i}@{b}professional astrology software@{ub}@{ui}, intended to be used by
    a single astrologer, or by a person interested in astrology.It may also
    be used by an @{i}amateur astronomer@{ui} to get an up-to-date picture of a sky.
    @{FG shine}If correctly used by a skilled person, it earns itself in a single day@{FG text}.
    (Otherwise one must spend some time reading the manual...)

  @{b}@{u}Name@{uu}@{ub}:
    "@{b}Asense @{i}is a Drosophila neural precursor gene and is capable of initiating
    sense organ formation@{ui}@{ub}." - the allegory is that this software is capable
    to make the end user aware of the @{i}@{b}astrological@{ub}@{ui} events that take place
    on the sky and of possible benefits that their analysis may bring.
      @{b}The other allegory is that the end users should be as numerous as
    the @{i}fruit flies@{ui} are@{ub}... :-)

  @{b}@{u}Documentation@{uu}@{ub}:
    For conveniance, the manual has been split in @{b}2 parts@{ub}, one that handles
    the @{b}GUI and astrology part@{ub} of the software, @{b}and@{ub} the other which focuses
    on @{b}astronomical data about the planets and their satellites, stars, and
    the solar system in general@{ub}.@{i}The portion of a guide devoted to astronomy
    contains no astrology at all@{ui}, except for the keywords about the objects.

  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}:
    - Amiga OS 2.04+ (or equivalent emulation),
    - Basic knowledge of astrology.

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}:
    - It is already installed in it's own directory.

  @{b}@{u}Localization@{uu}@{ub}:
    - built-in language is @{i}english@{ui}.
@endnode
///
///   Legal                                               //f
@node ASENSE-GENERAL-LEGAL "ASense - General: Legal"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV ASENSE-GENERAL-ABOUT
@NEXT ASENSE-GENERAL-FEATURES
@{b}@{u}Distribution@{uu}@{ub}:

  The ASense is a COMMERCIAL product and should be treated as such.
  It may NOT be shared, distributed, altered (except for archiving purposes),
  hacked, reversely engineered, copied (except for backup purposes) without a
  written (not electronic) permission by the @{"author" link ASENSE-GENERAL-CONTACT}.

  DEMO version of the software is freely distributable, if in original form.

  The user is warned that @{i}@{b}@{FG shine}updates would require the original executable to be
  present for updating@{FG text}@{ub}@{ui}. Keep a copy of this on a safe, write protected place.

@{b}@{u}Copyright@{uu}@{ub}:

  The @{b}ASense executable@{ub}, this guide (@{b}ASense-astrology.guide@{ub}), the other
  guides (@{b}ASense-astronomy.guide@{ub} and @{b}ASense-star-data.guide@{ub}), @{b}astro.library@{ub}
  and @{b}steph.library@{ub} are (c) 2005, 2006 by

    @{"Jim Sunrise" link ASENSE-GENERAL-CONTACT}.

     The documentation and program texts of ASense are subject to the
  same copyright as the program itself. This means NEITHER DOCUMENTATION
  NOR PROGRAM TEXTS MAY BE MODIFIED OR TRANSLATED IN ANY WAY, except for
  personal use.

     To avoid any misunderstanding: YOU MAY NOT @{i}translate@{ui} AND @{i}distribute@{ui}
  ASense program texts or documentation, unless I officially @{"appoint" link ASENSE-GENERAL-JOBS} you
  as the ASense translator.Unauthorized translations of program texts or
  documentation are illegal, violate this copyright, and will be deleted
  from public software sites.

  SPECIFICALLY, the following CHAPTERS FROM THE GUIDES may not be reproduced
  in whole or in parts on any publicly available form (written, printed or
  electronic) without a written (not electronic) permission by the @{"author" link ASENSE-GENERAL-CONTACT}:

    - the chapters about the @{"house systems" link ASENSE-DECIDE-HS} and about the @{"Altitude" link ASENSE-HS-ALTITUDE} house
      system (with all directly related pages),
    - the chapter about the @{"aspects" link ASENSE-SELECT-ASPECTS} and the @{"Special theory of aspects" link ASENSE-ASPECTS-QUANTUM-LINK}
      with all directly related pages including, but not limited to,
      the essay about the @{"orbs of the stars" link "ASENSE-ORBS-STARS"},
    - the essay '@{"Evolution of the Sun as a star" link "ASense-astronomy.guide/ASENSE-SUN-EVOLUTION"}',
    - the essay about the @{"delineation" link "ASense-astronomy.guide/ASENSE-PLANETS-DELINEATION"}. of the newly discovered planets
      and planetoids.

  SPECIFICALLY, the following CONCEPTIONS, invented by the @{"author" link ASENSE-GENERAL-CONTACT} of ASense,
  may not be integrated into other software product (@{b}especially not into a
  freeware one@{ub}), without a @{i}written@{ui} (not electronic) permission by the @{"author" link ASENSE-GENERAL-CONTACT}:

    - the @{"ASense Chart Style" link ASENSE-CHART_STYLE},
    - @{"Altitude" link ASENSE-HS-ALTITUDE} and @{i}altitude@{ui} house systems,
    - calculation and presentation of @{"aspects" link ASENSE-SELECT-ASPECTS}, as described in the chapter
      about them.

    Permissions to use the above mentioned documentations and inventions will
  be granted or refused on a case to case basis. The general intention isn't
  making a large amount of profit, but making the knowledge widely available
  for a modest reward for 17 years of work which stands behind this software.

  @{i}Note@{ui}: @{b}Under the laws of my country, electronic permission is not enough,
  even when certified by the court of some other country, therefore there
  must be a written permission as well@{ub}. Apologies for the inconveniance...

  @{b}crc.library@{ub} is a PD library, compiled by the author of the ASense from the
  code created by @{b}Dirk Stoecker@{ub} (Aminet:@{i}GetCRC@{ui}).The code is left unchanged.
  The library provides checksum capabilities with many different algorhitms.

  @{b}textfield.gadget@{ub} v3.1 is Copyright © 1995 Mark Thomas.
  @{b}easyrexx.library@{ub} v3.0 is Copyright © 1994,1995 Ketil Hunn.
  @{b}select.gadget@{ub}  v40.18 is Copyright © 2001 Massimo Tantignone

@{b}@{u}Given rights@{uu}@{ub}:

  Those who have legaly bought a (@{"guaranteed-to-be-unique" link ASENSE-GENERAL-UNIQUENESS}) 'copy' of the
  ASense may use it in their private astrology practice for profit making,
  may sell charts calculated by the ASense for profit, may post such charts
  on the web, providing that there is a clear notice about the origin of the
  charts, something like '@{i}@{b}The ASense chart style@{ub}@{ui}'; or '@{i}@{b}Generated by ASense@{ub}@{ui}',
  with attached link to some ASense-selling site under the word '@{i}ASense@{ui}'.
  This linking is not obligatory, but it may increase traffic to your site,
  which could be benefitial for you.
    You may also use the phrase '@{i}@{b}Charts created with Altitude house system@{ub}@{ui}'
  to advertise your services if you create charts for your clients with this
  house system.

@{b}@{u}Automatic chart generation for a web site@{uu}@{ub}:

    @{b}You may use an ARexx script for @{i}automatic@{ui} creation of charts on a web
  site, providing that you @{i}notify the @{"author" link ASENSE-GENERAL-CONTACT} of ASense about it@{ui} and that such
  a web site allows creation ONLY @{i}of those charts which are available by the
  ASense DEMO@{ui}, namely the @{i}natals from a limited time interval, with a limited
  number of stars@{ui}@{ub}. If you wish to provide more, you must purchase an additional
  @{b}LICENSE@{ub}. This would normally require payment of @{b}3% royalties@{ub} from the profit
  created by the site for a certain period, and perhaps some money in advance.
  @{b}The exact licensing details are open for negotiation on a case to case basis@{ub}.
    @{i}If such a script makes your site popular and consequently earns you some
  money as a result, then please consider making a small financial donation
  for the future development of ASense@{ui}. Financial donations can put a lot
  of weight on feature requests.

@{b}@{u}Disclaimer@{uu}@{ub}:

    The ASense comes with no warranty, either expressed or implied, except
  for the @{"GUARANTEE OF UNIQUENESS" link ASENSE-GENERAL-UNIQUENESS} as a @{"measure" link ASENSE-GENERAL-PROTECTION} against piracy.This means
  that there is NO GUARANTEE that ASense is fit for any specific purpose and
  no guarantee for any bug fixes, updates or help during error recovery!

    The ASense is provided "AS IS", which means that by installing ASense,
  the user accepts FULL responsibility for any damage or loss, mental or
  physical, that might occur through its direct or indirect usage or the
  inability to use it. USE THIS SOFTWARE ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN RISK! If the
  laws of your country state that the author of ASense is responsible
  no matter what, you are NOT allowed to use the ASense!

    EVEN THOUGH EVERY EFFORT HAS BEEN MADE TO MAKE ASense AS COMPATIBLE TO
  THE CURRENT STANDARDS AS POSSIBLE, I CANNOT RULE OUT THE POSSIBILITY THAT
  ASense HAS BUGS THAT HAVE HARMFUL SIDE EFFECTS ON YOUR SYSTEM OR ON OTHER
  MACHINES CONNECTED TO YOUR COMPUTER.

    I HEREBY REJECT ANY LIABILITY OR RESPONSIBILITY FOR THESE OR ANY OTHER
  CONSEQUENCES FROM THE USE OF ASense WHATSOEVER. THIS INCLUDES, BUT IS
  NOT LIMITED TO, DAMAGE TO YOUR EQUIPMENT, TO YOUR DATA, TO OTHER MACHINES
  YOUR CONPUTER IS CONNECTED TO, ANY EQUIPMENT CONNECTED TO THOSE HOSTS,
  PERSONAL INJURIES, FINANCIAL LOSS OR ANY OTHER KINDS OF SIDE EFFECTS.

@{b}@{u}Acknowledgements@{uu}@{ub}:
  - This research has made use of the SIMBAD database, operated at CDS,
    Strasbourg, France.

@{b}@{u}Credits@{uu}@{ub}:
  0. @{b}Jonathan Potter@{ub}
    - for DOpus v4.12 - the most amazing program ever written
  1. @{b}Dietmar Eilert@{ub}
    - for GoldEd v4.7.2, the best text editor on any platform.
  2. @{b}SAS/C development team@{ub}
    - for their SAS/C v6.58 C/C++ development package
    - for their codeprobe debugger (part of the SAS/C)
  3. @{b}Yvon Rozijn@{ub}   - for AWeb v3.0 web browser
  4. @{b}Holger Cruse@{ub}  - for Miami v2.1 TCP/IP stack
  5. @{b}Marcel Beck@{ub}   - for YAM v1.3.5 mailer
  6. @{b}Dirk Stoecker@{ub} - for xpk crunching package
  7. @{b}Nico Francois@{ub} - for reqtools.library
  8. @{b}Mark Thomas@{ub}   - for textfield.gadget v3.1
  9. @{b}Frank Toepper@{ub} - for Lupe
 10. @{b}Dimitri C. Keletsekis@{ub}
    - for GCView v2.0, the best picture displaying utility
 11. @{b}Ketil Hunn@{ub}    - for easyrexx.library v3.0
 12. @{b}Massimo Tantignone@{ub} - for select.gadget v40.18
@endnode
///
///   Features                                            //f
@node ASENSE-GENERAL-FEATURES "ASense - General: Features"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV ASENSE-GENERAL-LEGAL
@NEXT ASENSE-GENERAL-HISTORY
@{b}@{u}Features@{uu}@{ub} - whatever it does, it does it @{b}thoroughly@{ub}.

    The ASense has many options, but is still simple and easy to use.

@{b}@{u}Highlights@{uu}@{ub}:
  - @{FG shine}NEW!@{FG text} @{b}The Altitude house system@{ub}, designed to become the ultimate one
  - @{FG shine}NEW!@{FG text} @{b}Special theory of aspects@{ub}, applied and explained
  - ability to create exactly @{b}4400 chart types@{ub} with only few mouse clicks
    (by using a single date, that is), and @{b}272 different ways to draw them@{ub}
  - ability to generate @{b}28800 kinds of ephemeris@{ub} from a single (variable)
    set of objects, and to present each one @{b}in 70 different formats@{ub}
  - @{FG shine}NEW!@{FG text} @{b}The ASense chart style@{ub} (picture speaks a 1,000 words)
  - extended @{i}database of stars@{ui}, with many fine details about them
  - an up-to-date @{i}astronomical guide of objects@{ui} involved, with several
    additional interesting essays (@{i}'Evolution of the solar system'@{ui},...).
  - To comemorate the 150th anniversary from the birth of @{b}Nikola Tesla@{ub},
    his birth chart(s) were used as an example.

Features: (+ sign indicates an especially advanced and unique feature)
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
  NOTE: some of the features below are not used in astrology, but may
        be very useful for amateur astronomers and sky watchers.

  + @{FG shine}UNIQUE@{FG text} chart style, designed by a professional designer.
    '@{i}@{b}A picture speaks a thousand words@{ub}@{ui}.' - It has been taken good care that
    the chart picture presented to you at the end, really does exactly that.

    NOTE: @{b}ASense chart style is copyrighted. If you wish to reproduce it
    in your own software, then please read the '@{"Legal" link ASENSE-GENERAL-LEGAL}' part of the manual@{ub}.

  @{u}Zodiacs@{uu}:
  - tropical, sidereal, draconic, sidereal draconic zodiacs,
  + accurate and classic sidereal calculations,
  + accurate (sidereal or not) draconic zodiac (projected to lunar orbit),
  - 21 built-in classic sidereal zodiacs and 5 built-in accurate ones,
  - ability to define your own sidereal zodiacs (both accurate and classic).

  @{u}House systems@{uu}:
  + @{b}@{i}A@{ui}ltitude@{ub} (dynamic) and @{b}@{i}a@{ui}ltitude@{ub} (static) flavours of a house system which
    is designed by the author of this software with the aim to become the
    Ultimate house system. This is a very @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} and @{FG shine}UNIQUE@{FG text} feature,
  - Krusinski house system, a competitive newly proposed house system,
    the first one to use a complex transformation to compute the houses,
  - 17 other classical house systems (Topocentric, Gauquelin Sectors,
    Placidus, Morinus, Regiomontanus, Campanus, Alcabitus, Porphyry,
    Neo-Porphyry, Koch (a.k.a. Birthplace), Horizon (a.k.a. Azimuth),
    Meridian (a.k.a. Axial Rotation), Whole, Vehlow, Ptolemy,
    Equal from MC, Equal from Asc.

  - Angles (Asc, MC, Desc, IC), Vertex, Equatorial Asc.

  @{u}Charts@{uu}@{u}@{uu}:
  - topocentric, geocentric, heliocentric or solar system barycentric charts,
  - apparent, astrometric, true (a.k.a geometric), or virtual positions,
  - ability to turn on/off light-time correction, gravity deflection,
    aberration, precession, nutation and refraction,
  - traditional or accurate (with nutation eliminated) sidereal modes.

  - natal chart (surprise, surprise),
  - offset charts - ability to manualy do a step-by-step chart animation by
    - time (seconds/minutes/hours/days/months/years/centuries/millenia),
    - geo. longitude (hours/minutes/seconds/degrees/arcmins/arcsecs),
    - geo. latitude (degrees/arcmins/arcsecs),
    - altitude (meters/hectometers/kilometers),
    - cycles (solar/lunar returns/solar enneads/progr./directions/transits),
  - ability to quickly review the natal chart and to return to offset chart,
  - ability to cast offset charts in a ring.

  @{b}Data input@{ub}:
  - ability to enter data as a single string, instead of many separate
    entries. This allow faster manipulation and improves observability.
  - support for different date formats.
  - ability to require the data to be properly graded with EXTENDED Roden
    rating(coordinates are to be graded too) to be able to create charts.
  - ability to refuse to cast complex charts with poorly graded data.

    @{u}Presentation@{uu}:
    - ability to choose the view (sky as viewed from a northern/southern
      hemisphere or a combined view, depending on a location from a chart)
    - ability to chose a presentation mode:
      - normal (1 coordinate) (standard chart type),
      - ringed (2 coordinates, 1 radial, 1 circular), with aspects, or
      - conic (realistic views of both hemispheres of the sky, without aspects
        optionally with stars (2 charts, side-by-side)
      - ability to choose a second (radial) coordinate separately
        (pair of first/declination/latitude/altitude/refracted altitude)
        (This allows charts of long. vs decl. type, ringed or conic.)

    @{u}Cyclic charts@{uu}:
    - true/mean anomalic/sidereal/tropical/draconic solar returns
    - true/mean anomalic/sidereal/tropical/draconic solar enneads
    - true/mean anomalic/sidereal/tropical/draconic/synodic lunar returns
    - true/mean sidereal/tropical/synodic MC returns
    - secondary returns (kinetic returns, anlunars)
    - phase returns for sun and moon (a.k.a. synodic/draconic) (obsolete term)
    - planetary returns (indirectly supported by time stepping)

    - primary, secondary, tertiary and minor progressions
      + total of *@{b}861 subtypes of progressions@{ub}@{b}@{ub}* are available

    - primary, secondary and tertiary directions of solar/lunar/Asc/MC arc,
      + total of *@{b}3420 subtypes of directions@{ub}* are available

    + subtypes number depends on a choice of projection (ecl/equ/hor/drac/3D),
      and also on definitions of terms year/month/day (tropical, sidereal...)

    - normal and precession corrected transits (sidereal transits)

    - ability to show cyclic charts in a ring around the natal,
    - ability to quickly alter the data for both natal (main) and cyclic charts,
    - ability to find and produce cyclic charts valid for a given date/time,
    - ability to find and produce cyclic charts valid for a given
      date/time/place.

    @{u}Comparison charts@{uu}:
    - synastry charts (6 types),
    - swapped houses (tables),
    - mutual aspects (between a chart in a ring and the main (inner) one).
    - Davison relationship charts
      - ability to use midpoints of individual geographical coordinates or
                       midpoints on a great circle
    - composite charts
      - ability to merge individual coordinates or
                to find a great circle merge
    - coalescent charts
      - coalesc on a selected plane (ecl/equ/hor/drac/great circle (3D))
      - ability to coalesc only one, or both angular spheric coordinates
    - ability to show Davison relationship/composite/coalescent chart in
      a ring around the natal (and to find mutual aspects, swap houses...)

    @{u}Stars@{uu}:
    - star chart (chart of all selected stars, with distances depicted),
    - ability to turn on/off different coloring for retrograde stars,
    - ability to turn on/off plotting of stars and/or displaying of their data,
    - ability to show the stars from a cyclic chart (or natal chart) plotted
      on a chart as well, with fancy, meaningfull graphics.

  @{u}Ephemeris generation@{uu}:
  - versatile ephemeris generator, 5 grades of accuracy (0.1° .. 0.1" of arc),
  - compact or normal output
  - ephemeris for interval of time
  - ephemeris for month, 2 months or a year
  - ephemeris for a chart's date/time/place, or for current transits
  - ephemeris for user selectable time steps (from 1 second to 1 millenia)
  - ephemeris for noon, midnight, or user adjustable time borders
  - events: ingresses, stationary times (with accuracy estimates)
  - weekdays, sidereal times
  - absolute julian date, deltat, true and mean ecliptic obliquity,
    nutation in longitude, nutation in obliquity, inclination of lunar orbit
  + ephemeris for 27 different data parameters calculable by this software:
    - ecliptical (longitudes (with and without zodiac signs), latitudes,
      daily speeds in longitudes and latitudes),
    - draconic (within the lunar plane) ('longitudes' and 'latitudes' when
      draconic zodiac is selected),
    - equatorial (R.A., declinations, daily speeds in R.A, and declinations),
    - horizontal (azimuths, altitudes, *refracted* altitudes, daily speeds of
      azimuths, altitudes and refracted altitudes),
    - daily maximums and minimums of altitudes and refracted altitudes,
    - distance and radial speed
    - times of risings and settings,
    - times of meridian transits (MC and IC transits)
    + times of culminations and of lowest altitudes
  - ability to save ephemeris on a selected file

  @{u}Data Settings@{uu}:
  - ability to adjust the rounding of
    - arcs (minutes, seconds, no rounding)
    - astronomy units (1, 3, 9 digits)
    - magnitudes (1 or 2 digits)
    - percentages (percents, promiles, no rounding)
    - text (full, abbrev.),

  @{u}Data@{uu}:
  - absolute julian date, deltat, true and mean ecliptic obliquity,
    nutation in longitude, nutation in obliquity, inclination of lunar orbit

  - times of risings and settings,
    - risings and settings for upper limb, for center or for a lower limb,
  - times of meridian transits (MC and IC transits)
  + times of culminations and of lowest altitudes
    - angle crossings on a given date, on previous date, on next date, or
      on ±half a day around of a given time (±12 hours),

  - phase angles and percentages, elongations, apparent diameters, magnitudes,
  - defined orbs (as adjusted by the user)

    @{u}Coordinates@{uu}:
    - ecliptical (longitudes (with and without zodiac signs), latitudes,
      daily speeds in longitudes and latitudes),
    - draconic (within the lunar plane) ('longitudes' and 'latitudes' when
      draconic zodiac is selected),
    - equatorial (R.A., declinations, daily speeds in R.A, and declinations),
    - horizontal (azimuths, altitudes, *refracted* altitudes, daily speeds of
      azimuths, altitudes and refracted altitudes),
    - daily maximums and minimums of altitudes and refracted altitudes,
    - distance and radial speed
    - cartesian ecliptic coordinates with speeds,
    - cartesian draconic coordinates with speeds.
    - placements within (all) 88 astronomical constellations

    - house positions (upto 6 decimal places)
    - swap houses positions (chart comparison technique)

    @{u}Data about aspects@{uu}:
    - delta to 100%, actual angles, percentages,
    - orbs of aspects, total orbs, halfed orbs,
    - ability to sort aspects (by type, objects, attributes, percentage).

    @{u}Data about the stars (from stellar catalogs)@{uu}:
    - Proper names, synonyms, translations and cross-catalog references
      (Bayer/Flamsteed/HR/GCVS-NSV/FKS/HIP/HD/DM/ADS/GC)
    - Rot. speeds, parallaxes, errors of parallaxes, distances in ly/pc,
      errors of distances in ly/pc,
    - variability type(s), periods, epochs of max light, durations of eclipses
    - max/min/abs/U-B/B-V/R-I magnitudes,
    - order of components,
    - spectral types of all components, very detailed, with roughly noted
      sizes of mutual orbits and other peculiarites

    @{u}Derived data about the stars@{uu}:
    - all of the above mentioned coordinates,
    - temperatures, radii, visual and total luminosities,
    - bolometric correction (difference between total and visual luminosities),
    - center of comfort zone (distance from a central star which receives the
      same amount of insolation as the Earth does, the liquid-water zone).

    - ability to sort stars (by name, HR index, constellation, magnitude,
      spectral type, longitude, latitude, R.A., declination, vicinity,
      azimuth, altitude, house position).

  @{u}Objects@{uu}:
  - sun, moon, planets, true and mean lunar nodes, fortuna, angles (objects)
  - ability to select which objects are to be included in the chart.
  + 400 named stars (all of them), much more astronomical details about stars
    than in other astrology programs, in other to allow better understanding
    and felling of their influence (the naming isn't everything, something lies
    in appearance too).
  - ability to select which groups of stars are to be checked for importance
    (choices by magnitude (6 options) and/or by properties (named, bright,
     nearby, close, variable, zodiac)).

  @{u}Accuracy of built-in ephemeris@{uu}:
  - 0.05" of arc, except for Moon, which is 0.5" of arc (a speed compromise).
  @{u}Range of built-in ephemeris@{uu}:
  - 8000 years (4000 BC - 4000 AD)

  @{u}Aspects@{uu}:
  - 25 different aspect types (first 12 series, parallels),
  - ability to select which aspects are to be included in the chart,
  - adjustable planetary orbs,
  + @{FG shine}UNIQUE@{FG text} aspect calculation algorithm that handles everything automatically:
    - @{i}applying@{ui} / @{i}separating@{ui} aspects (with different handling of each),
    - @{i}ingoing@{ui} / @{i}outgoing@{ui} (a.k.a. @{i}sinister@{ui} / @{i}dexter@{ui} aspects),
    + every aspect has a separate orb, based on the harmonics theory.These are
      not directly adjustable, since they were made to fully depend on the orbs
      of planets involved,
    - aspects with or without latitude (a.k.a. 2D / 3D aspects),
    - aspects in different planes (2D mode): ecl/equ/hor/drac/3D (great circle)
    - ability to force conjunctions only to be computed in 2D (useful for stars)
  - ability to turn on/off aspects to angles,
  - ability to turn on/off aspects to stars,
  - ability to turn on/off @{i}very-tight-orbs@{ui} mode (all orbs are halfed, useful
    for messy and low importance charts, like horary ones),
  - ability to adjust the threshold of aspects and to reject the wide ones,
  - ability to calculate mutual aspects between a main chart and a ringed one,
  - ability to draw aspects without displaying the data table about them.

  @{u}Documentation@{uu}:
  - @{i}@{b}Special theory of aspects@{ub}@{ui} - an almost complete theory of aspects, which
    gives answers to all outstanding questions of 'Why?', except that it
    doesn't gives the sizes of the orbs... These have to be empirically
    determined first (the options exist for that) in order for the theory
    to be able to expand to include the results. The stellar orbs are the
    important ones and are still being analyzed. This is very @{FG shine}UNIQUE@{FG text}.
  - guide of planets and stars (astronomy guide)
  - an up-to-date @{i}astronomical guide of objects@{ui} involved, with several
    additional interesting essays (@{i}destiny of the solar system@{ui},
    @{i}history of the Earth@{ui},...).
  - asynchronous online help
  - tips-of-the-day for beginners
  - example for novices
  - FAQ file

  @{u}GUI@{uu}:
  - friendly GUI, designed by a professional designer (hundreds of options,
    yet most charts are only one or two mouse clicks away),
  - no need to remember the meaning of fancy icons (everything has labels),
  - ability to control textfields from a numeric keypad
  - ability to quickly access important functions by menu shortcuts
  - ability to quickly access the most important functions by GUI buttons
  - ability to present upto 4 charts at once and to compare them mutually.
  - ability to zoom in the fine (messy) details.
  - ability to change the screen mode.
  - hover help about objects (just point an object to find it's details).

  @{u}Input / output@{uu}:
  - ability to save the reports
  - ability to alter the reports
  - ability to save the picture of the chart
  - ability to configure everything and save the settings
  - ability to adjust the colors (and to save the adjustments)
  - ability to iconify (menufy) and to start several copies of the program
    simultaneously

  @{u}Databases@{uu}:
  - Extensive database support.
  - all data is forced to be graded with extended Roden rating.
  - ability to recall any chart data entered during a session with a single
    keypress.
  - ability to save and reload data strings entered during a session as
    history files
  - ability to easily merge the history files with databases
  - ability to add records to a database, and to comment them
  - ability to filter the records by any recorded parameter, including
    comments
  - 22 databse filtering types, including case sensitive searches
  - ability to use multiple set of filters at the same time
  - ability to use inclusive or exclusive filtering
  - ability to sort loaded database by any recorded parameter.
  - ability to browse the records from history and databse buffers with
    a single keypress, showing only those which are not blocked by filtering

  @{u}Scripts@{uu}:
  - ability to control ASense from ARexx
  - ability to run ARexx scripts from ASense
  - ability to record sequences and to save them as ARexx macros
  - an integrated shell for ARexx commands
  - at least 38 ARexx commands with many arguments

  @{u}Support@{uu}:
  + ability to easily hunt bugs and write debuging reports to developer.
  + statistics of usage (the record is kept about how many times a user has
    used every gadget and menu item available). This data may be valuable
    to developer to create a better explained and accesible application.
    User is asked to send this data as feedback when writing bugreports
    or support messages to developer.

  @{u}Tech@{uu}:
  + extremely optimised algorithms (the author is a professional optimiser)
  + very small and compact size (low footprint): fits on floppy, works on
    10 years old hardware without problems, flawlessly. Requires only 2Mb.
  - requires AmigaOS v2.0.4+.
  - can work without a HD.

  - ability to quit and vanish without traces left in the memory :-)
@endnode
///
///   History                                             //f
@node ASENSE-GENERAL-HISTORY "ASense - General: History"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV ASENSE-GENERAL-FEATURES
@NEXT ASENSE-HISTORY-REVISIONS
@{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}:

  @{"Revisions" link ASENSE-HISTORY-REVISIONS} - bugfixes, updates, new features, cosmetic changes.
  @{"Versions" link ASENSE-HISTORY-VERSIONS} - major reconstructions, platform / language changes.

  @{"Known bugs" link ASENSE-HISTORY-BUGS} - bugs, bug-looking features, bugs in 3rd party tools.

  @{"ToDo" link ASENSE-HISTORY-TODO} - what needs to be done and plans for the future.

@endnode
///
///     Revisions                                         //f
@node ASENSE-HISTORY-REVISIONS "ASense - History: Revisions"
@TOC ASENSE-GENERAL-HISTORY
@PREV ASENSE-GENERAL-HISTORY
@NEXT ASENSE-HISTORY-VERSIONS

  @{u}Legend@{uu}:
    @{b}CBF@{ub} / @{b}CWA@{ub} - compatibility bugfix/workaround
          @{FG shine}@{b}NEW@{ub}@{FG text} - new feature
          @{b}FIX@{ub} - bugfix
    @{b}+++@{ub} /   @{b}+@{ub} - large/small improvement
      (@{i}empty@{ui}) - very small cosmetic change

  Average rate of development: 2 changes/week, maintained from v3.0 to v4.0.

  @{b}@{u}v4.0a@{uu}@{ub}: Minor documentation update. @{i}@{b}1 change@{ub}@{ui} in 68k version.  (Nov-2006)
    @{b}CBF@{ub} - Old v3.? config files are now correctly loaded by 68k version too.

  @{b}@{u}v4.0@{uu}@{ub}: Version change, old OS version supported, @{i}@{b}51 changes@{ub}@{ui}.  (Oct-2006)
    @{FG shine}FIX@{FG text} - light-time correction was faulty for geoc/topoc positions. (FIXED)
          The bug caused errors in longitudes of planets upto 20" of arc. :(
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - True positions of @{i}stars@{ui} (without light-time corr) are now computable.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - Reduced errors in obliquity of ecliptic for very ancient times by an
          order of magnitude. (This affects dates before 1750 BC only.)
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - Stars sometimes weren't updated correctly upon side change. Fixed.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - On specific occasions, not all prominent stars were drawn. Fixed.
      @{b}+@{ub} - When selecting '@{i}Names@{ui}' instead of '@{i}Glyphs@{ui}' the zodiac signs and the
          aspect signs and names in aspect table also get converted to their
          appropriate abbreviations. This is useful for exporting chart data
          to people without the fonts used by ASense (i.e. general public).
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - Swap house positions for impossible situations are now set to zero.
          Those are, for instance, the house positions in a heliocentric chart.
          (Previously, unrelated old cached values were incorrectly returned.)
      @{b}+@{ub} - After zooming/unzooming of the window, the textfields are cleared.
    @{FG shine}@{b}NEW@{ub}@{FG text} - Adapted to work on ancient @{b}AmigaOS 2.0.4+@{ub} (@{b}V37@{ub}) to support UAE users.
    @{b}CWA@{ub} - The supplied files are no longer crunched by imploder in order to
          support the (buggy) @{i}SystemPatch@{ui} v2.96. Read the @{"ASense.warning" link "ASense.warning/Main" 0}.
    @{b}+++@{ub} - added '@{b}Ow@{ub}' button to turn ON/OFF overwriting in the string gadget.
    @{FG shine}@{b}NEW@{ub}@{FG text} - added (@{"extended" link ASENSE-GENERAL-DATA_GRADING}) @{i}Roden@{ui} rating of data.
    +++ - complex charts cannot be cast any more without sufficiently good data.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - @{b}Added ARexx port and 38 commands@{ub} with many attributes. The ASense is
          now fully controllable from ARexx.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - ability to run ARexx scripts from ASense.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - @{b}ability to record sequences and reuse them later, or to save them
          as ARexx macros.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - an integrated shell for ARexx commands.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - Added @{"Krusinski" link ASENSE-HS-KRUSINSKI} house system.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - @{b}Extensive @{"database" link ASENSE-MENUPROJECT} support@{ub}.
          (Filtering, sorting, browsing and selecting the recorded entries.)
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - added DATA_DIR and DB_FILE tooltypes to support @{i}@{b}external databases@{ub}@{ui}.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - ability to recall any data entered during a session by a simple
          keypress.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - ability to record entered data strings as @{i}@{b}history files@{ub}@{ui} and to
          recall them in subsequent sessions, or to integrate them (or
          parts of them) into global databases.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - palette changes were never saved with config as supposed.Fixed.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - @{i}exe@{ui}.datatype now supported. Not used by ASense, however.
          (Used by multiview to examine the internals of an executable file.
           Previously, the list of used libraries was obscured from view.)
      @{b}+@{ub} - allowed opening of the screen with non-interleaved (fragmented) bitmap
          to support users with fragmented or low memory conditions.
    @{b}+++@{ub} - screen depth of @{b}4@{ub} is now allowed to support old V37 graphics.library
          and users with less memory.
      @{b}+@{ub} - The ASense screen is now PUBLIC. As a consequence,
      @{b}+@{ub} - the ASense can be started multiple times, with all windows
          appearing on the same screen simultaneously (as visitors);
      @{b}+@{ub} - the related system requesters now appear on the ASense screen.
        - Added a few more '@{i}tips@{ui}'.
    @{b}CWA@{ub} - added TIME_ZONE tooltype to allow usage without @{i}locale@{ui}.library.
        - @{i}iffparse@{ui}.library is now @{i}optional@{ui} (no clipboards without it).
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - hover help object pointers weren't cleared upon window closing. Fixed.
        - reordered 1st row of buttons on the right side to allow fitting of an
          extra button ('@{b}Ow@{ub}').
        - updated guides and readmes.
      @{b}+@{ub} - the help system now calls the guide files in @{i}@{b}asynchronous@{ub}@{ui} mode.This
          allows more flexibility in use and allows tracking of IO errors.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - atpres is now updated on altitude change by offsets.
        - atpress is displayed in mBars, µBars or nBars (if sufficiently low).
    @{b}+++@{ub} - changed font in input string from @{i}@{b}as_grn@{ub}@{ui} to @{i}@{b}grn@{ub}@{ui}. Thus, instead of
          astrological symbols, standard letters are present, which may be
          @{i}usefull for typing in non-english names of charts and places@{ui}. Users
          of Latin-2 and other charsets have to replace the grn font with
          something that they like and use, but it must be of identical size.
      @{b}+@{ub} - Extended max length of input string to 137 chars to allow entering
          of longer combinations of name/place strings (space for text around
          the chart allows max of 32/28 chars, respectively).
          However, the input string length in tooltypes (user default strings)
          is limited to 127 chars, which is the fixed limit set by the AmigaOS.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - hover help erasing was 2 pixels 2 high. Fixed. (This bug wasn't
          noticed before, because the above line was usually empty.)
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - hover help data is now erased prior to chart save call.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - some body pointers were left uncleared during hiding. Fixed.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - zodiac menu flags weren't correctly updated after config reload.
        - side text about aspects removed from charts without aspects.
      @{b}+@{ub} - Forked threshold of aspects to applying and separating ones.
        - a lot of code rewritten, some optimizations in the process.
    @{FG shine}NEW@{FG text} - '@{b}-@{ub}' button gained functionality - ability to reset the offsets.
      @{b}+@{ub} - added handling of CTRL-C signal.
    @{b}+++@{ub} - added handling of different @{i}date format@{ui}s (@{b}DD­Mon, Mon DD, DD/MM@{ub}).
      @{b}+@{ub} - '/' and '­' (@{b}ASCII 173@{ub}) are now allowed as delimiters in strings.

  ***************************************************************************

  @{b}v3.6@{ub}: Bugfix-update version, @{i}@{b}3 changes@{ub}@{ui}.                      (May-2006)
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - The bottom toolbar was invisible in non-PAL resolutions.Fixed.
    @{FG shine}@{b}NEW@{ub}@{FG text} - Added '@{i}Tips-of-the-day@{ui}' in the window's title to help beginners.
    @{FG shine}@{b}NEW@{ub}@{FG text} - Added FAQ file.

  @{b}v3.5@{ub}: Regular 6-months-update version, @{i}@{b}35 changes@{ub}@{ui}.           (May-2006)
    @{FG shine}@{b}NEW@{ub}@{FG text} - @{b}The ephemeris range has doubled@{ub}.
          The limits are now set to -4000 .. 4000 years.The match with JPL
          ephemeris is quite close, but the JPL ephemeris only go to ±3000
          years, so the true accuracy of the remaining 1000 years is unknown.
    @{b}+++@{ub} - @{b}update of deltat values, change of formulas for precession,
          nutation, sidereal time and obliquity of ecliptic to more recent
          theories@{ub}. This has upgraded accuracy a little.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - Delta t formula for ancient times was totally wrong.@{i}Replaced@{ui}.
    @{b}@{FG shine}+++@{FG text}@{ub} - Revision of delta t calculation algorhitms has lead to the great
          increase in the accuracy of eclipse predictions.The ASense now
          computes and shows the historically recorded eclipses quite well.
      @{b}+@{ub} - some physical constants are improved to their newer values.
          This gave another small upgrade of accuracy on several places.
      @{b}+@{ub} - as a consequence of the above changes, @{i}t0 of the Sassanian
          sidereal zodiac is updated@{ui} (change of +6 s of time was added)
      @{b}+@{ub} - some code optimisations in astro.library gave a small improvement
          of the speed of computations
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - Absolute julian day was displayed in @{i}UT@{ui}, instead of @{i}ET@{ui}. Fixed.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - user defined t0 was erroneusly passed as @{i}UT@{ui}, without conversion
          to ET. Fixed.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - House positions for sid(ereal) zodiacs were wrong.Fixed.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - @{i}Refraction@{ui} is now @{i}disabled for geocentric view@{ui} as being meaningless.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - Residual underlining of star names obtained with hover help removed.
          The underlining doesn't remain on screen anymore when the mouse moves.
    @{b}+++@{ub} - @{b}default orbs of lunar nodes, Chiron and Juno updated to empirically
          measured values@{ub}. @{i}The orb of Chiron was measured to have @{b}extension@{ub}
          in a direction of it's tail, but this still remains to be handled@{ui}.
          The influence of distances on orbs remains to be studied...
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - orbs of DESC and MC were reversed with each other (fixed)
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - setting of orbs routine revised to handle pressing of ENTER
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - debug notes for setting of orbs of angles was wrong (fixed)
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - distance of 'Infinity' is added to display tables for axes
    @{b}@{FG shine}NEW@{FG text}@{ub} - @{i}@{b}added ability to change screen mode@{ub}@{ui}.
          Depending on a selected screen mode, the GUI tries to adapt itself.
          Several font sizes were created in order to support these changes.
        - created topazastro3 11 fontsize (was missing in v3.0)
        - as_grn.font replaced with the as_grn3.font (baseline changed)
    @{b}CBF@{ub} - fixed a problem of '@{i}missing topaz 9@{ui}' which occured on OS 3.9
          due to a bug in the corresponding diskfont.library.
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - stats keeping were incorrect.@{i}Fixed@{ui}.
    @{FG shine}@{b}NEW@{ub}@{FG text} - added monitoring of the usage of @{i}house systems@{ui} and @{i}zodiacs@{ui} to stats
        - added notification on built-in CPU & FPU support to screen title
        - added '@{i}v@{ui}' in front of a version number
      @{b}+@{ub} - overruled '@{i}no stars@{ui}' flag when @{i}star chart@{ui} is wanted
      @{b}+@{ub} - default value of orbs changed for @{i}lunar nodes@{ui}
    @{b}+++@{ub} - revised the way @{i}dual cycle steps@{ui} were handled
        - slight improvement of the drawing of @{i}exact dexter aspects@{ui}
        - @{i}hover help@{ui} improved
      @{b}+@{ub} - forced gadget help to be ON on registration window :-)
    @{b}FIX@{ub} - sysrep could have failed if it's tooltype was wrong (fixed)
      @{b}+@{ub} - old version notification added to order sheet
        - update of the @{i}ASense-astrology@{ui}.guide
        - update of the @{i}ASense-astronomy@{ui}.guide

  @{b}v3.0@{ub}: First public release.                                  (Dec-2005)
@endnode
